Autoscale Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)

What is Autoscaling?

Autoscaling hosting continuously monitors the performance of your website or application. When demand spikes, additional resources such as CPU, memory, or bandwidth are automatically provisioned.

By dynamically adjusting resources, autoscaling ensures that your site or application remains responsive and performs well, regardless of fluctuations in traffic.

What type of applications does Autoscale support?

Autoscale comes with 80+ one-click apps for you to install, including WordPress, Joomla!, Drupal, Laravel, PrestaShop, OpenCart, Matomo and more.

What happens if I exceed my disk space or bandwidth allowance?

Each of our plans includes a set amount of disk space and bandwidth. Our platform continues to scale seamlessly even if you exceed your plan 's allocated resources, ensuring your website remains up and running. If you go over your plan limits, you will incur small overage fees based on your additional usage: $1 per 1 GB of extra disk space and $0.05 per 1 GB of extra bandwidth. You can also choose to upgrade to the next plan for more included resources.

Does mailbox usage impact my storage allowance?

No, mailbox usage does not impact your storage allowance for website hosting. Our mail platform operates separately from our web hosting platform, so mailbox storage is not included in your website hosting storage allowance. Each mailbox comes with a 10GB limit, and this is all included at no additional cost to you.

What is CDN pre-caching?

Pre-caching improves the performance and speed of websites and applications by loading resources ahead of time. This process involves storing certain assetssuch as HTML files, CSS stylesheets, JavaScript files, images, and other content before they are actually needed.

Our CDN use pre-caching to store content on edge servers, speeding up delivery times by serving content from a location geographically nearer to the user. This results in faster load times and a smoother user experience.

What is High-Availability Hosting?

High-availability hosting is built on infrastructure that minimizes downtime by distributing resources across multiple servers. This redundancy ensures that users experience minimal to no interruption in service.

High-Availability Hosting can handle hardware failures, spikes in traffic, or other unexpected events without affecting the end user.

How do I migrate to 20i?

Migrating to 20i is easy. Use our in-house Migration Center to automatically migrate your sites and applications from your current provider. If you prefer a manual migration, simply contact our Support Teamavailable 24/7/365and theyll happily handle it for you.

Whats the difference between Autoscaling and a Cloud Server?

With a Cloud Server youre allocated dedicated hardware, giving you additional control over the hosting environment. With Autoscaling, infrastructure automatically scales and allocates additional resources to your sites to handle traffic spikes ideal for cost-efficiency and handling unpredicatable demand.
